`.github/workflows/` defines CI/CD automation for this repo — currently a single pipeline that publishes a visualization site to GitHub Pages on push to `main` or manual dispatch.

The workflow's contract with the rest of the repo is implicit and fragile: it expects a `viz-data` binary in the Cargo workspace that writes `out/viz-data.json`, and expects `viz/index.html` to read that file by its current relative path. Renaming either the binary target, its output path, or `viz/index.html` breaks the deploy silently (the build step won't fail, only the published site will be wrong). It also depends on a toolchain pin (`rustup show`) existing at the repo root and on `pages`/`id-token: write` permissions being enabled in repo settings — neither of which this file controls.

No intent.md exists for this directory to check against.